22/11/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu urged more Italians to invest in Albania, during a meeting with Italian counterpart Giorgio Napolitano in Rome on Tuesday (November 21st). 
In addition to investments, Moisiu said they talked about economic co-operation and regional issues.
In other news, a new poll by the Institute for International Studies -- with support from the European Commission in Tirana -- suggests an overwhelming majority of Albania's citizens back EU integration. 
According to the results, reported on Wednesday, 92.5% of respondents want Albania in the EU, up nearly 9% from last year. 
(Albanian News, Korrieri, Gazeta Shqiptare - 22/11/06)
